# Literature Review

## 1. Introduction
Ultrasound-triggered drug delivery systems have been extensively studied for targeted therapies.

## 2. Current Technologies
- Microbubbles
- Liposomes
- Ultrasound-responsive hydrogels

## 3. Gaps in Research
- Controlled release mechanisms
- Long-term biocompatibility

## 4. Conclusion
Further innovation is needed in ultrasound sensitivity and system miniaturization.
